cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV 

This paper focuses on the problem of learning locomotion skills on real-world robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of reinforcement learning and hierarchical learning also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of model predictive control and dynamics models suggests a focus on control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of sensory noise and different environments suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) for perception and localization.
